# Google Sign-In (optional). Get a Web Client ID from Google Cloud Console:
# 1. Go to https://console.cloud.google.com/
# 2. Create or select a project → APIs & Services → Credentials
# 3. Create credentials → OAuth 2.0 Client ID → Application type: Web application
# 4. Add Authorized JavaScript origins: http://localhost:5173 (and your production URL)
# 5. Copy the Client ID and set it below. Restart the dev server after changing .env.
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=

# Supabase (free tier) — user profiles + verification. Get URL and anon key from:
# 1. Go to https://supabase.com/dashboard → New project
# 2. Project Settings → API: copy Project URL and anon public key
# 3. SQL Editor → run the SQL in supabase/schema.sql (profiles + verification_codes tables)
# 4. Deploy Edge Functions (see below) for email verification.
# 5. Set the vars below and restart the dev server.
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=

# Email verification (optional). Without this, users see "use 123456 for testing".
# 1. Get an API key from https://resend.com/api-keys (free tier: 100 emails/day).
# 2. In Supabase Dashboard → Edge Functions → set secret: RESEND_API_KEY = your key.
# 3. Deploy: supabase functions deploy send-verification-code verify-code --no-verify-jwt
